    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2011-10-12</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2011-11-09T21:29:54Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Easy Voting Act of 2011 - Amends the Help America Vote Act of 2002 to: (1) require a minimum early voting period of 14 days preceding a federal election for states offering early voting, (2) prohibit an election official from requiring an individual to provide a state-based identification as a condition of registering to vote or of receiving or casting a ballot in any federal election, and (3) require states to make same-day voter registration and change of address service available at the polling place on the date of election. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Easy Voting Act of 2011</title>
    <titles>
      <item>
        <titleType>Display Title</titleType>
        <title>Easy Voting Act of 2011</title>
      </item>
      <item>
        <titleType>Official Title as Introduced</titleType>
        <title>To amend the Help America Vote Act of 2002 to require any State offering an early voting period in elections for Federal office to make the period available for the entire 14-day period that precedes the date of the election, to prohibit States from imposing identification requirements on individuals who wish to vote or register to vote who are not otherwise required to provide identification under such Act, and for other purposes.</title>
        <billTextVersionName>Introduced in House</billTextVersionName>
        <billTextVersionCode>IH</billTextVersionCode>
      </item>
